"32N":{"department":"MUSIC","number":"32N","title":"Sculpting with Sounds, Images, and Words","description":"Preference to freshmen. Contemporary culture abounds in multimedia forms, in which sounds, images and words are interwoven in unique ways. What are their individual and combined powers? How would you harness them? Participants face these questions in creative projects as well as through in-class viewing, analysis and debates, readings, guest lectures and student presentations. The seminar is taught at the Center for Computer Research in Music and Acoustics where students have access to new media technologies.","min_units":3,"max_units":3,"gers":["DB-Hum","WAY-CE"],"primary":[[{"instructors":[],"meeting-times":[{"days":[true,false,true,false,false],"start":"13:15:00","end":"14:30:00"}]}],[],[]]},
"34N":{"department":"MUSIC","number":"34N","title":"Performing America: The Broadway Musical","description":"Musical theater as a site for the construction of American identity in the twentieth century to the present. Issues of class, race, gender, and sexuality; intersections with jazz, rock, and pop; roles of lyricist, composer, director, choreographer, producer, performers. Individual shows (Showboat, Oklahoma, South Pacific, Guys and Dolls, West Side Story, Wicked, Bloody Bloody Andrew Jackson, Book of Mormon), show tunes in jazz performance, film musicals, and television. Opportunities for performance and attendance at local productions.","min_units":3,"max_units":3,"gers":["DB-Hum","WAY-AII","WAY-CE"],"primary":[[],[],[{"instructors":[],"meeting-times":[{"days":[false,true,false,true,false],"start":"16:15:00","end":"17:45:00"}]}]]},
